# Universal Utilities

The universal package contains utility functions that work in both browser and Node.js environments without specific platform dependencies.

## Key Files

- [filterFalsy.ts](mdc:packages/universal/filterFalsy.ts): Filters out falsy values from an array
- [isBoolean.ts](mdc:packages/universal/isBoolean.ts): Type guard for boolean values
- [isError.ts](mdc:packages/universal/isError.ts): Type guard for Error objects
- [isFunction.ts](mdc:packages/universal/isFunction.ts): Type guard for functions
- [non-nullable.ts](mdc:packages/universal/non-nullable.ts): Utility for filtering out null and undefined values
- [removeSpecialCharacters.ts](mdc:packages/universal/removeSpecialCharacters.ts): String utility to remove special characters
- [sleep.ts](mdc:packages/universal/sleep.ts): Utility for creating delays in asynchronous code
- [getDate.ts](mdc:packages/universal/getDate.ts): Date utility functions
- [yyyy-mm-dd.js](mdc:packages/universal/yyyy-mm-dd.js): Date formatting utility

## Usage

These utilities can be used in any JavaScript/TypeScript environment without worrying about platform-specific APIs. They are suitable for projects that target both browser and Node.js environments.
